						<summary>

						<p>Slab lying in front of the ruined temple of Śiva in the fort.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1607, Krōdhana, Phālguṇa śu. 15,</hi> corresponding to 1686 A.D., January 28 Sunday. Also refers to <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1607, Kshaya, Māgha, śu. 15.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records the obeisance of Gangi-Reḍḍi and Bucchireḍḍi to the god Siddhiśvaradēva and the goddess Kāmakshamma.</p>						

						</summary>
